## 5. Risk Assessment & Mitigation

| # | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| R1 | Port 5002 already in use on dev machine | Medium | Medium | Catch `EADDRINUSE` in `app.listen` error callback and print clear message with `lsof -i :5002` hint. For POC, a process.exit(1) is acceptable. |
| R2 | `@types/express` v5 vs. `express` v4 type drift | Low | Medium | Pin to `@types/express@^4.17` matching `express@^4.21`. Verify with `npm run build`. |
| R3 | Static file path breaks when running from compiled `dist/` | Low | High | Use `path.join(__dirname, "..", "public")` ‚Äî resolves project-root in both ts-node and compiled modes (verified: `src/../public` === `dist/../public`). |
| R4 | Missing `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` now fails at server boot instead of at first request ‚Äî worse UX than CLI | Low | Low | Existing `config/env.ts` throws on import with a clear message naming the env var. Acceptable fail-fast; server log will show exactly why. |
| R5 | Orchestrator return-shape change accidentally breaks an unseen consumer | Very Low | Low | `grep -r "runOrchestrator" src/` confirms `src/index.ts` is the only consumer, and it's being deleted. |
| R6 | XSS via agent response containing HTML/script | Low (local-only) | Medium | Use `textContent` exclusively ‚Äî never `innerHTML`. Documented in ¬ß4 Task 2. |
| R7 | Browser fetch to relative `/api/chat` fails if user opens `file:///` instead of `http://localhost:5002` | Medium (user error) | Low | Only serve index.html via Express. The `express.static` + `GET /` pattern means the user must hit the server; no loose file. |
| R8 | Orchestrator classifier call + sub-agent call = ~2s-5s latency visible to user | High | Low | Loading indicator + disabled input (¬ß4.2) makes waiting explicit. Streaming is out of scope. |
| R9 | Sample prompts drift from `src/data/prompts.ts` over time | Medium | Low | Add a code comment in HTML referencing the source file. Accept coupling for POC. Future migration to `/api/samples` is a 10-LOC change. |

