### Task 4 ‚Äî Verbose logging

**Additive changes inside `runAgent.ts`:**

```ts
let turn = 0;
while (true) {
  turn += 1;
  console.log(`\n‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ Turn ${turn} ‚Äî API call ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ`);

  const response = await anthropic.messages.create({ ... });
  state.addAssistantMessage(response.content);

  for (const block of response.content) {
    if (block.type === "tool_use") {
      console.log(`‚Üí tool_use: ${block.name}`);
      console.log(`  input: ${JSON.stringify(block.input)}`);
    }
  }

  if (response.stop_reason === "tool_use") {
    for (const block of response.content) {
      if (block.type !== "tool_use") continue;
      const result = dispatchTool(block.name, block.input as Record<string, unknown>);
      console.log(`‚Üê tool_result (${block.name}): ${result}`);
      state.addToolResult(block.id, result);
    }
    continue;
  }

  if (response.stop_reason === "end_turn") {
    const text = /* ...as before... */;
    console.log(`\n‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ Final answer ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ\n${text}\n‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ`);
    return text;
  }
  // ...
}
```

**Decisions:**
- Use Unicode box-drawing characters (`‚îÅ`) for section separators ‚Äî readable in any modern terminal, no ANSI color dependency.
- Arrows `‚Üí` (outgoing tool call) and `‚Üê` (incoming tool result) make direction of data flow visually obvious in the trace.
- Log tool_use blocks as they're observed in the response (one pass), dispatch in a second pass ‚Äî keeps the visual narrative: "here's what Claude wants, here's what the tool returned."
- Return value still goes through `console.log` from the CLI entrypoint ‚Äî the CLI sees the *same* text the function returns, so stdout piping still works for downstream use (the trace logs go to stdout too, which is fine for a POC; only a concern if we ever need to pipe clean output).

**Estimated complexity:** Trivial (~15 LOC added, 15 min).

